{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '<!-- ROTOM IS NOT A LEGENDARY POKÉMON. DO NOT ADD IT TO THE PAGE. -->\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Electric|type2=Ghost}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Rotom}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Electric|prevnum=478|prev=Froslass|nextnum=480|next=Uxie|round=none}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Rotom}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Rotom\n|jname=ロトム\n|jtranslit=Rotomu\n|tmname=Rotom\n|forme=6\n|form2=Heat Rotom\n|form3=Wash Rotom\n|form4=Frost Rotom\n|form5=Fan Rotom\n|form6=Mow Rotom\n<!--The Rotom Pokédex is not a form-->\n|image2=479Rotom-Heat.png\n|image3=479Rotom-Wash.png\n|image4=479Rotom-Frost.png\n|image5=479Rotom-Fan.png\n|image6=479Rotom-Mow.png\n|ndex=479\n|sdex=152\n|karea=Mountain\n|kdex=068\n|typebox=6\n|type1=Electric\n|type2=Ghost\n|form2type1=Electric\n|form2type2=Fire\n|form3type1=Electric\n|form3type2=Water\n|form4type1=Electric\n|form4type2=Ice\n|form5type1=Electric\n|form5type2=Flying\n|form6type1=Electric\n|form6type2=Grass\n|category=Plasma\n|height-ftin=1\'00"\n|height-m=0.3\n|weight-lbs=0.7\n|weight-kg=0.3\n|abilityn=1\n|abilitylayout=1\n|ability1=Levitate\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Amorphous\n|eggcycles=20\n|evtotal=2\n|evsa=1\n|evsp=1\n|expyield=154\n|oldexp=132\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|gendercode=255\n|color=Red\n|catchrate=45\n|body=01\n|pokefordex=rotom\n|generation=4\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Rotom\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ロトム\'\'\' \'\'Rotom\'\') is a dual-type {{2t|Electric|Ghost}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation IV]].\n\nWhile it is not known to [[Evolution|evolve]] into or from any other Pokémon, it has the ability to possess the motors of certain appliances and [[List of Pokémon with form differences#Rotom|change forms]].\n*When it does not possess an appliance, it is {{2t|Electric|Ghost}}-type.\n*When it possesses a {{wp|microwave oven}}, it becomes \'\'\'Heat Rotom\'\'\', and is {{2t|Electric|Fire}}-type.\n*When it possesses a {{wp|washing machine}}, it becomes \'\'\'Wash Rotom\'\'\', and is {{2t|Electric|Water}}-type.\n*When it possesses a {{wp|refrigerator}}, it becomes \'\'\'Frost Rotom\'\'\', and is {{2t|Electric|Ice}}-type.\n*When it possesses an {{wp|mechanical fan|electric fan}}, it becomes \'\'\'Fan Rotom\'\'\', and is {{2t|Electric|Flying}}-type.\n*When it possesses a {{wp|lawn mower|lawnmower}}, it becomes \'\'\'Mow Rotom\'\'\', and is {{2t|Electric|Grass}}-type.\n\nAdditionally, in [[Generation VII]], it has the ability to possess a special [[Pokédex]] and become the [[Rotom Pokédex]]. In [[Generation VIII]], Rotom has the ability to possess a smartphone that doubles up as a Pokédex and becomes the [[Rotom Phone]].\n\nDepending on the game, its form can be changed at will in [[Rotom\'s Room]] in the [[Team Galactic Eterna Building]], Rotom\'s Room in [[Silph Co.]], the store room in [[Shopping Mall Nine]], on the second floor of [[Professor Sycamore]]\'s Lab in [[Lumiose City]], in [[Professor Birch]]\'s Lab in [[Littleroot Town]], or in the basement of the Pokémon Research Lab on Alola\'s {{rt|1|Alola}}. In [[Generation IV]], Rotom changes back to its normal form when taken into the [[Union Room]] or [[Wi-Fi Club]], or when deposited in the {{pkmn|Day Care}}.\n\nIn [[Generation IV]], it is {{2t|Electric|Ghost}}-type regardless of its form.\n\n==Biology==\n[[File:Brock and Rotom.png|thumb|220px|left|Rotom transforming]]\nRotom has a body of plasma and is shaped like a lightning rod. There is a whitish blue aura of electricity around it that forms lightning bolt-shaped appendages. It has teeth, and its unique, blue eyes have a dividing line across them. [[DP105|As seen in the anime]], Rotom will often pull pranks on unsuspecting people. [[XY081|Also seen in the anime]], Rotom has the ability to [[time travel]].\n\n[[File:Rotom parts.png|thumb|220px|Rotom and the appliances]]\nRotom has the ability to enter and control appliances. Starting in {{v2|Platinum}}, it also has five extra forms, each based on a household appliance, which can be accessed by possessing specific appliances. The possessed appliances are based on a {{wp|microwave oven}} (Heat Rotom), {{wp|washing machine}} (Wash Rotom), {{wp|refrigerator}} (Frost Rotom), {{wp|mechanical fan|electric fan}} (Fan Rotom), and a {{wp|lawn mower|lawnmower}} (Mow Rotom). When Rotom changes form, its eyes and electric aura change colors and its aura appendages take on different shapes: red with oven mitts as Heat Rotom, blue with clothespins as Wash Rotom, purple with lightning bolts as Frost Rotom, yellow with air curls as Fan Rotom, and green with a ripped strip as Mow Rotom.\n\nWhile Rotom typically use their abilities to make mischeif, some Rotom have taken to inhabiting electronics with the intent of helping others, as seen in [[Generation]]s {{gen|VII}} and {{gen|VIII}}. The [[Rotom Pokédex]], found in [[Alola]], and [[Rotom Phone]]<!-- and [[Rotomi]]-->, found in [[Galar]], are some examples. These particular forms allow Rotom to [[talking Pokémon|speak human languages]]. \n\n<gallery>\n479Rotom-Pokédex.png|A [[Rotom Pokédex]]\n479Rotom-Phone.png|A [[Rotom Phone]]\n</gallery>\n{{-}}\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Oak Rotom.png|thumb|250px|Rotom in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===In the main series===\n====Major appearances====\n=====[[Professor Oak\'s Rotom]]=====\n{{an|Professor Oak}} {{pkmn2|caught}} a Rotom on [[Torom Island]] in \'\'[[BW128|To Catch a Rotom!]]\'\'. Rotom is a prankster, often scaring {{Ash}} by appearing over the video phone whenever he calls Professor Oak. It also appeared in [[Professor Oak\'s Pokémon Holo Caster]] in the {{series|XY}}, helping Professor Oak with his explanation, and often laughing at him when he gets hurt.\n\n====={{an|Rotom Pokédex}}=====\nA Rotom inhabiting Ash\'s [[Alola]]n [[Pokédex]] debuted in \'\'[[SM003|Loading the Dex!]]\'\'. As a Pokédex, Rotom has access to data about many different Pokémon species, but it often hurts itself and others by trying to see a Pokémon do a certain action after reading its information. In [[SM146]], it remained in Alola while Ash returned [[Pallet Town|home]] to work with the [[Aether Foundation]].\n\n=====Other=====\nRotom debuted in \'\'[[DP105|Get Your Rotom Running!]]\'\' in all of its different forms, toying around with {{Ash}} and {{ashfr}}.\n\nTwo Rotom appeared in \'\'[[BW128|To Catch a Rotom!]]\'\' alongside {{OP|Professor Oak|Rotom}}, where they took on all of their different forms.\n\nA Rotom appeared in \'\'[[XY081|Rotom\'s Wish!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Weston]]. It took the form of Wash, Mow, and Frost Rotom. In the episode, it was able to defeat [[Mantle]] and his {{p|Krookodile}} with the assistance of Ash and {{ashfr}}.\n\nA Rotom appeared in \'\'[[SM057|The Dex Can\'t Help It!]]\'\', where it took the form of a Wash Rotom. An accident caused by [[Ash\'s Pikachu]] resulted in Rotom being ejected from the washing machine and getting swapped with Rotom Pokédex. Eventually, the Rotom were swapped back to their original places.\n\n====Minor appearances====\nA Rotom appeared as an image in \'\'[[XY091|A Performance Pop Quiz!]]\'\'.\n\n<gallery>\nHeat Rotom anime.png|Heat Rotom in the {{pkmn|anime}}\nWash Rotom anime.png|Wash Rotom in the anime\nFrost Rotom anime.png|Frost Rotom in the anime\nFan Rotom anime.png|Fan Rotom in the anime\nOak Rotom Mow.png|Mow Rotom in the anime\nRotom Pokédex anime.png|Rotom Pokédex in the anime\n</gallery>\n\n====Pokédex entries====\n{{Animedexheader|Sinnoh}}\n{{Animedexbody|DP105|Rotom|Ash\'s Pokédex|Rotom, the Plasma Pokémon. Rotom plays practical jokes, which it carries out by embedding its plasma body in electronic devices.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Diamond & Pearl\'\'|Sinnoh}}\n{{Animedexheader|Unova}}\n{{Animedexbody|BW128|Rotom|Ash\'s Pokédex|Rotom, the Plasma Pokémon. With a body made of plasma Rotom is able to permeate various kinds of electrics devices, causing all sorts of problems.}}\n{{Animedexf