hunder}}\n}}\n|}\n\n===Evolution===\n{{Evobox-1\n|type1=Electric\n|type2=Ghost\n|pictype=art\n|no1=479\n|name1=Rotom\n|type1-1=Electric\n|type2-1=Ghost}}\n\n===Forms===\n{{Evobox/Formes\n|type2-disp=Ghost\n|sprite1=479Rotom\n|name1=Rotom\n|type1-1=Electric\n|type2-1=Ghost\n|forme=6\n|forme1=Rotom\n|loc1=Normal\n|sprite2=479Rotom-Heat\n|forme2=Heat Rotom\n|type1-2=Electric\n|type2-2=Fire\n|loc2=Microwave oven\n|sprite3=479Rotom-Wash\n|forme3=Wash Rotom\n|type1-3=Electric\n|type2-3=Water\n|loc3=Washing machine\n|sprite4=479Rotom-Frost\n|forme4=Frost Rotom\n|type1-4=Electric\n|type2-4=Ice\n|loc4=Refrigerator\n|sprite5=479Rotom-Fan\n|forme5=Fan Rotom\n|type1-5=Electric\n|type2-5=Flying\n|loc5=Electric fan\n|sprite6=479Rotom-Mow\n|forme6=Mow Rotom\n|type1-6=Electric\n|type2-6=Grass\n|loc6=Lawnmower}}\n\n===Sprites===\n{{Spritebox/Header|type=Electric|type2=Ghost}}\n{{Spritebox/NA|gen=IV}}\n{{Spritebox/4/6Forms|ndex=479|form1=O|form2=W|form3=R|form4=F|form5=L}}\n{{Spritebox/5/6Forms|ndex=479|form1=O|form2=W|form3=R|form4=F|form5=L}}\n{{Spritebox/6/6Forms|ndex=479|form1=O|form2=W|form3=R|form4=F|form5=L}}\n{{Spritebox/7/6Forms|ndex=479|form1=O|form2=W|form3=R|form4=F|form5=L}}\n{{Spritebox/Footer|479|Rotom}}\n\n==Trivia==\n* When Rotom is encountered in the [[Old Chateau]] in {{3v2|Diamond|Pearl|Platinum}}, the music is the same as {{pkmn2|Legendary}} encounters, although it is not classified as one. Rotom is, to date, the only non-Legendary Pokémon to do this.\n* Rotom\'s alternate forms, along with {{p|Arceus}}\'s forms, were the only alternate forms of a Pokémon not featured in [[Pokémon Mystery Dungeon: Explorers of Sky]]. However, despite being introduced a year before the game was released like Rotom, {{p|Shaymin}} and {{p|Giratina}}\'s alternate forms made an appearance in the game.\n* Rotom is tied with {{p|Tynamo}} as the [[List of Pokémon by weight|lightest]] {{type|Electric}} Pokémon.\n* Rotom was the first Pokémon mentioned to be {{DL|List of Pokémon by gender ratio|genderless}} in the {{pkmn|anime}}.\n* Rotom and each of its forms were designed by different designers:\n** Rotom\'s base form was designed by [[Ken Sugimori]].\n** Heat Rotom was designed by [[Lee HyunJung]].\n** Wash Rotom was designed by [[Hiroki Fuchino]].\n** Frost Rotom was designed by [[Hironobu Yoshida]].\n** Fan Rotom was designed by [[Motofumi Fujiwara]].\n** Mow Rotom was designed by [[Yusuke Ohmura]].\n\n====Generation V type change====\n* Rotom is the only Pokémon to have its type changed to a type that was not newly introduced.\n* No other Pokémon has the same [[type]] [[List of Pokémon with unique type combinations|combination]] as Rotom\'s base form, Heat Rotom, Frost Rotom, or Mow Rotom.\n* Despite becoming part {{type|Flying}}, Fan Rotom retains the Ability Levitate, being the only Flying-type Pokémon with this Ability. As its Flying type already makes it immune to {{type|Ground}} moves, its Ability is effectively useless under normal conditions.\n** In [[Inverse Battle]]s, Fan Rotom is still protected from Ground moves due to Levitate, making it the only Flying-type Pokémon to not be affected by Ground-type moves in these battles.\n* All of Rotom\'s appliance forms except Mow Rotom are tied for or have the fewest weaknesses of all Pokémon of their secondary types.\n* All of Rotom\'s appliance forms are the lightest Pokémon of their secondary types.\n\n===Origin===\nRotom appears to be [[List of references to Pulseman|based on]] {{wp|Pulseman}}, who was designed by Pokémon designer [[Ken Sugimori]], although it may also be inspired by the unexplained phenomenon of {{wp|ball lightning}}. Its Pokédex entry brings to mind {{wp|gremlin}}s. Its possession of other objects may be based on {{wp|poltergeist}}s or {{wp|tsukumogami}}. Rotom may also be an embodiment of electronic "{{wp|magic smoke}}". It may also be based on {{wp|electrical energy}}.\n\n====Name origin====\nRotom is \'\'motor\'\' backwards; this may refer to the fact that motors make many appliances function, while Rotom makes them fail.\n\nIn {{game|Platinum}}, an old notebook in [[Rotom\'s Room]] describes how a person discovered and named the first known Rotom. It appeared out of a lawn mower\'s motor, and the person named it Rotom due to this origin.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Electric|type2=Ghost\n|ja=ロトム \'\'Rotom\'\'|jameaning=From \'\'motor\'\' spelled backwards\n|de=Rotom|demeaning=Same as Japanese name\n|fr=Motisma|frmeaning=From \'\'{{tt|moteur|engine}}\'\' and \'\'plasma\'\'\n|es=Rotom|esmeaning=Same as Japanese name\n|it=Rotom|itmeaning=Same as Japanese name\n|ko=로토무 \'\'Rotomu\'\'|komeaning=Transliteration of Japanese name\n|zh_cmn=洛托姆 \'\'Luò Tuō Mǔ\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=Transliteration of Japanese name\n|ru=Ротом \'\'Rotom\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n<br clear="left">\n{| style="float:left"\n|-\n| style="vertical-align:top" |\n\'\'Heat Rotom\'\'\n{{langtable\n|color={{electric color}}|bordercolor={{fire color}}\n|ja=ヒートロトム \'\'Heat Rotom\'\'\n|zh_cmn=加熱洛托姆 \'\'{{tt|Jiārè Luòtuōmǔ|Heat Rotom}}\n|da=Varme-Rotom\n|fi=Lämpö-Rotom\n|fr=Motisma Chaleur\n|de=Hitze-Rotom\n|it=Rotom Calore\n|ko=히트로토무 \'\'Heat Rotom\'\'\n|no=Varme-Rotom\n|pl=Rotom Grzewczy\n|pt_br=Rotom Calor\n|pt_eu=Rotom Calor\n|es=Rotom Calor\n|sv=Värme Rotom\n|vi=Rotom Nhiệt}}\n| style="vertical-align:top" |\n\'\'Wash Rotom\'\'\n{{langtable\n|color={{electric color}}|bordercolor={{water color}}\n|ja=ウォッシュロトム \'\'Wash Rotom\'\'\n|zh_cmn=沖洗洛托姆 \'\'{{tt|Chōngxǐ Luòtuōmǔ|Wash Rotom}}\n|da=Vaske-Rotom<!-- not mentioned in XY081 -->\n|fi=Pesu-Rotom\n|fr=Motisma Lavage\n|de=Wasch-Rotom\n|it=Rotom Lavaggio\n|ko=워시로토무 \'\'Wash Rotom\'\'\n|no=Vaske-Rotom{{tt|*|SM057}}<br>Wash Rotom{{tt|*|XY081}}\n|pl=Rotom Piorący\n|pt_br=Rotom Lavagem{{tt|*|SM056-present, TCG}}<br>Wash Rotom{{tt|*|XY081}}\n|pt_eu=Rotom Lavagem\n|es=Rotom Lavado\n|sv=Tvätt Rotom\n|vi=Rotom Tẩy Rửa\n}}\n| style="vertical-align:top" |\n\'\'Frost Rotom\'\'\n{{langtable\n|colo